status: General position of the sensor relative to to the object under study.

definition (en): Remote-sensing image was made from a device located on the surface of a body, usually a planet or moon.
Remote-sensing image was made from a device above the surface of a body, generally in the atmosphere, an aircraft, balloon, or some other airborne device.
Remote-sensing image was made from a device in space. Spaceborne sensors are those located outside the primary layers of an atmosphere (usually in orbit) and beyond.
Altitude of the sensor is not applicable to the image.
Altitude of the sensor from which the image was made is not known.
Altitude of sensor other than surface, airborne, spaceborne.
